ce:section.ce:para:
C-dots are highly biocompatible nanomaterial, which show exceptionally multifaceted applications in biological world. Our experimental results reveal that C-dots and C-dots–DA were highly biocompatible as compared to the DA alone. At this concentration, range from 1 to 10μgmL−1 (Fig. 3
                        ), the cell survival percentage was nearly about 95% for C-dots–DA conjugate and 74% for DA alone. Many reports suggest that C-dots are highly biocompatible for many cell models [5,33]. Our results showed an excellent biocompatibility of C-dots–DA in Neuro 2A cells (Table 1
                        ).
